        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-12-20 11:25:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> Patch Set 6: Code-Review-2\n> \n> Will the resources deployed at startup be deployed to each tenant? From looking at the code review looks like they will continue to be deployed as today, i.e. not deployed to any tenant. I would imagine this would be a big problem regarding multi-tenancy as those resources can be edited by a user in any tenant affecting users across all tenants\n> \n> While control is introduced at the point of creating a resource/service, there is no control on a lot of APIs, for example will be possible to create a service in one tenant and add a resource instance to it from another tenant.\n> The SDC BE code reads data types, node types etc from the DB during the execution of API calls, there is no control introduced to ensure these internal calls only access info from the correct tenant.\n> \n> Have you considered introducing the tenant based control at a lower level, e.g. in the DB (for example different keyspaces per tenant) or in the data access layer (catalog-dao) rather than in the servlets. This would be a more robust solution that covers all APIs and avoids to need to include tenant based filtering in all the different servlets\n> \n> There is no real isolation of data, for example, what would happen if a user creates a service which has the same name as already exists in another tenant? A user can delete resources/services from any tenant\n\n\nHello Micheal,\n\nAs discussed we will take up these activity (isolation of data) and UE activity in next phase.\n\ncould you please help us to close this",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
